.TH _PRINTF 3 "March 2026" "Holberton School" "_printf manual"

.SH NAME
_printf \- custom implementation of the printf function

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.BI "int _printf(const char *" format ", ...);"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function writes formatted output to the standard output.

It supports the following format specifiers:

.TP
.B %c
Print a single character.

.TP
.B %s
Print a null-terminated string. If the argument is NULL, "(null)" is printed.

.TP
.B %%
Print a literal percent sign.

.TP
.B %d
Print a decimal integer.

.TP
.B %i
Print an integer in base 10.

If an unknown specifier is encountered, the percent sign and the
specifier character are printed as-is.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of characters printed on success.

Returns -1 if
.I format
is NULL

.SH FILES
.TP
.I main.h
Header file containing the prototype for
.B _printf
and helper functions.

.TP
.I printf.c
Contains the main
.B _printf
function.

.TP
.I handlers.c
Contains functions for supported specifiers.

.TP
.I integer_handlers.c
Contains integer printing functions.

